[{"id":"KMF000000","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"qti-layout-row\"> <div class=\"qti-layout-col12\"> <div class=\"prompt\"> <p class=\"dap_body\">The cosine function is a horizontal translation of the sine function with <span aria-label=\"sin open parentheses x plus pi over 2 close parentheses equals cos x\"><math alttext=\"sin open parentheses x plus pi over 2 close parentheses equals cos x\"><semantics><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>cos</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span>. Which of the following identities can be used to verify this identity by direct substitution and evaluation without additional algebraic manipulation?</p> </div> </div> </div>\n","rubricRef":"KMF000000_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p><span class=\"dap_body\">​The sum identity for sine</span></p>","<p><span class=\"dap_body\">​The sum identity for cosine</span></p>","<p><span class=\"dap_body\">​The double-angle identity for sine</span></p>","<p><span class=\"dap_body\">​The double-angle identity for cosine</span></p>"],"answer":"A-95119"}]